WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.381 align:middle line:90%


00:00:07.381 --> 00:00:09.140 align:middle line:84%
Hey, everybody.
Welcome to "Mind Shift."

00:00:09.140 --> 00:00:11.420 align:middle line:10%
In this episode, we are
discussing that power of women

00:00:11.420 --> 00:00:14.320 align:middle line:10%
to change the world with
the extraordinary performer,

00:00:14.320 --> 00:00:17.490 align:middle line:10%
writer and activist Eve Ensler,
and the incredibly precocious

00:00:17.490 --> 00:00:19.730 align:middle line:10%
Islamic feminist Jerin Arifa.

00:00:19.730 --> 00:00:21.170 align:middle line:84%
Eve recently won
a harrowing battle

00:00:21.170 --> 00:00:23.190 align:middle line:84%
against cancer, described
in her latest book,

00:00:23.190 --> 00:00:24.760 align:middle line:90%
"In the Body of the World."

00:00:24.760 --> 00:00:26.640 align:middle line:84%
At the same time, she has
helped women in the Congo

00:00:26.640 --> 00:00:28.820 align:middle line:84%
to overcome a situation
of tremendous oppression,

00:00:28.820 --> 00:00:31.230 align:middle line:84%
and build a new
school, City of Hope.

00:00:31.230 --> 00:00:33.505 align:middle line:84%
She's extraordinarily inspiring,
and it's a great pleasure

00:00:33.505 --> 00:00:34.926 align:middle line:90%
to speak with her.

00:00:34.926 --> 00:00:37.391 align:middle line:90%
