-Hey, everybody.

00:01:30.586 --> 00:01:32.387 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to "Mind Shift."

00:01:32.387 --> 00:01:33.220 align:middle line:90%
This is Daniel Pinchbeck.

00:01:33.220 --> 00:01:35.760 align:middle line:10%
Our first guest this week
is the amazing activist,

00:01:35.760 --> 00:01:38.670 align:middle line:10%
playwright, creator of "The
Vagina Monologues," Eve Ensler.

00:01:38.670 --> 00:01:40.600 align:middle line:10%
Thank you so much
for joining us.

00:01:40.600 --> 00:01:42.410 align:middle line:10%
NARRATOR: Author of
"The Vagina Monologues,"

00:01:42.410 --> 00:01:45.030 align:middle line:10%
Eve Ensler is an American
playwright, performer,

00:01:45.030 --> 00:01:46.660 align:middle line:10%
feminist, and activist.

00:01:46.660 --> 00:01:48.730 align:middle line:10%
Her current book, "In
the Body of the World,"

00:01:48.730 --> 00:01:50.610 align:middle line:10%
has been regarded
as an unforgettable,

00:01:50.610 --> 00:01:54.120 align:middle line:10%
raw, and powerful story of by
the New York Times Book Review.

00:01:54.120 --> 00:01:56.840 align:middle line:84%
She is the creator of V-Day,
a global activist movement

00:01:56.840 --> 00:01:59.050 align:middle line:90%
to stop violence against women.

00:01:59.050 --> 00:02:01.360 align:middle line:84%
The movement to date has
raised over $80 million,

00:02:01.360 --> 00:02:05.010 align:middle line:84%
and has funded over 12,000
community-based anti-violence

00:02:05.010 --> 00:02:08.979 align:middle line:84%
programs and safe houses
in the Congo, Haiti, Kenya,

00:02:08.979 --> 00:02:11.870 align:middle line:84%
South Dakota, Egypt,
and Iraq, providing

00:02:11.870 --> 00:02:14.770 align:middle line:84%
women sanctuary from
abuse, genital mutilation,

00:02:14.770 --> 00:02:15.830 align:middle line:90%
and honor killing.

00:02:15.830 --> 00:02:18.930 align:middle line:84%
She was born in New
York City, and in 1999,

00:02:18.930 --> 00:02:20.450 align:middle line:84%
was awarded the
Guggenheim Fellowship

00:02:20.450 --> 00:02:23.378 align:middle line:90%
Award in playwriting.

00:02:23.378 --> 00:02:25.838 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:02:25.838 --> 00:02:27.320 align:middle line:84%
-Hey, Eve.
-Hi.

00:02:27.320 --> 00:02:29.551 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much for
joining us on "Mind Shift."

00:02:29.551 --> 00:02:31.230 align:middle line:84%
-Thrilled to be here.
-I really appreciate it.

00:02:31.230 --> 00:02:32.020 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:02:32.020 --> 00:02:34.230 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, maybe just
tell us a little

00:02:34.230 --> 00:02:36.120 align:middle line:84%
about your recent
trajectory, your new book,

00:02:36.120 --> 00:02:38.661 align:middle line:84%
and the work you're doing
with One Billion Rising.

00:02:38.661 --> 00:02:39.360 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:02:39.360 --> 00:02:40.650 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'm really
happy to be here.

00:02:40.650 --> 00:02:45.120 align:middle line:84%
I think this show's awesome,
and it's a really great idea.

00:02:45.120 --> 00:02:48.790 align:middle line:10%
Well, "In the Body of
the World" is a memoir,

00:02:48.790 --> 00:02:52.990 align:middle line:10%
and it's kind of
based on a combination

00:02:52.990 --> 00:02:55.730 align:middle line:10%
of factors and inspirations.

00:02:55.730 --> 00:02:57.710 align:middle line:90%
One was cancer.

00:02:57.710 --> 00:03:01.320 align:middle line:84%
I had stage three/four
uterine cancer.

00:03:01.320 --> 00:03:03.930 align:middle line:84%
And that compelled
me or propelled me

00:03:03.930 --> 00:03:07.320 align:middle line:84%
into a whole new
trajectory, both in my body,

00:03:07.320 --> 00:03:08.940 align:middle line:90%
and coming into my body.

00:03:08.940 --> 00:03:13.461 align:middle line:84%
Because I went through a huge
kind of apocalypse in my body.

00:03:13.461 --> 00:03:14.160 align:middle line:90%
You know, I--

00:03:14.160 --> 00:03:15.626 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it sounded
like that from the book.

00:03:15.626 --> 00:03:16.810 align:middle line:90%
it sounded very extreme.

00:03:16.810 --> 00:03:17.970 align:middle line:90%
It was very, very extreme.

00:03:17.970 --> 00:03:22.270 align:middle line:84%
And through the process of
all that happening, what

00:03:22.270 --> 00:03:24.220 align:middle line:84%
began to happen
is I begin to have

00:03:24.220 --> 00:03:27.110 align:middle line:84%
this very transformative
experience that's

00:03:27.110 --> 00:03:29.680 align:middle line:90%
kind of taken me by surprise.

00:03:29.680 --> 00:03:32.050 align:middle line:84%
And it really began
with the diagnosis,

00:03:32.050 --> 00:03:35.670 align:middle line:84%
and shot me into this
state of-- I was on my way

00:03:35.670 --> 00:03:38.410 align:middle line:84%
to Haiti to do work
in Haiti, and I

00:03:38.410 --> 00:03:40.460 align:middle line:84%
suddenly heard, you
have stage four cancer,

00:03:40.460 --> 00:03:41.890 align:middle line:90%
stage three cancer.

00:03:41.890 --> 00:03:44.070 align:middle line:84%
And three days, I was
in nine hour surgery,

00:03:44.070 --> 00:03:45.730 align:middle line:84%
and all kinds of
organs were removed.

00:03:45.730 --> 00:03:49.130 align:middle line:84%
But I think what was amazing
about the whole experience is

00:03:49.130 --> 00:03:52.340 align:middle line:84%
that for so much of my life,
I had been searching for a way

00:03:52.340 --> 00:03:53.770 align:middle line:90%
back into my body.

00:03:53.770 --> 00:03:56.160 align:middle line:84%
I think, for many of us who
have been traumatized when we're

00:03:56.160 --> 00:03:58.880 align:middle line:84%
younger, or were abused,
or sexually attacked,

00:03:58.880 --> 00:04:01.487 align:middle line:84%
or whatever-- I think all
of us are traumatized.

00:04:01.487 --> 00:04:03.220 align:middle line:84%
I don't think there's anyone
on the planet who's not

00:04:03.220 --> 00:04:06.070 align:middle line:84%
traumatized, but I think some
people have secondary trauma,

00:04:06.070 --> 00:04:07.470 align:middle line:84%
and some people
have primary trauma.

00:04:07.470 --> 00:04:13.320 align:middle line:84%
And I had survived both
rape and enormous violence

00:04:13.320 --> 00:04:14.020 align:middle line:90%
from my own father.

00:04:14.020 --> 00:04:17.029 align:middle line:84%
And I think at a very
young age, I left my body.

00:04:17.029 --> 00:04:18.680 align:middle line:84%
It was just too
terrible place, and too

00:04:18.680 --> 00:04:20.339 align:middle line:90%
terrifying a place to inhabit.

00:04:20.339 --> 00:04:24.240 align:middle line:84%
And as a result of that,
I left or lost connection

00:04:24.240 --> 00:04:27.890 align:middle line:84%
with the Earth, with just
the basis of existence,

00:04:27.890 --> 00:04:30.520 align:middle line:84%
and was floating
for a long time.

00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:34.130 align:middle line:84%
And I think what happened
when I was diagnosed

00:04:34.130 --> 00:04:37.180 align:middle line:84%
and went through this
surgery is I landed.

00:04:37.180 --> 00:04:38.940 align:middle line:90%
I woke up, and I was in my body.

00:04:38.940 --> 00:04:41.630 align:middle line:84%
I had tubes coming
out of every port.

00:04:41.630 --> 00:04:42.370 align:middle line:90%
I had ports.

00:04:42.370 --> 00:04:43.930 align:middle line:90%
I had catheters.

00:04:43.930 --> 00:04:45.300 align:middle line:90%
I had machines.

00:04:45.300 --> 00:04:48.760 align:middle line:84%
And it was the first
time I was ever in here.

00:04:48.760 --> 00:04:52.230 align:middle line:84%
And that began this incredible--
which I can only describe

00:04:52.230 --> 00:04:55.980 align:middle line:84%
as a mystical experience
of beginning to land more,

00:04:55.980 --> 00:04:59.910 align:middle line:84%
and more, and more inside my
body, which was landing me more

00:04:59.910 --> 00:05:02.360 align:middle line:84%
and more inside the Earth,
and more and more connected

00:05:02.360 --> 00:05:03.740 align:middle line:90%
to everything around me.

00:05:03.740 --> 00:05:08.430 align:middle line:84%
And by the time I got to chemo,
which was down the journey

00:05:08.430 --> 00:05:11.210 align:middle line:84%
after infections
and operations, I

00:05:11.210 --> 00:05:13.780 align:middle line:84%
was really terrified of
chemo, the idea of putting

00:05:13.780 --> 00:05:16.270 align:middle line:90%
poison into my bloodstream.

00:05:16.270 --> 00:05:16.990 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:05:16.990 --> 00:05:18.250 align:middle line:90%
It just felt claustrophobic.

00:05:18.250 --> 00:05:19.310 align:middle line:90%
It felt end of the world.

00:05:19.310 --> 00:05:22.650 align:middle line:84%
And I had this brilliant
therapist who's

00:05:22.650 --> 00:05:23.880 align:middle line:90%
really a visionary person.

00:05:23.880 --> 00:05:25.770 align:middle line:90%
And she just showed up one day.

00:05:25.770 --> 00:05:29.610 align:middle line:84%
I notice one chapter you talked
about imagining all the reasons

00:05:29.610 --> 00:05:31.070 align:middle line:84%
why you might have
gotten this cancer, as

00:05:31.070 --> 00:05:33.570 align:middle line:84%
if there was some reason
for this to have happened.

00:05:33.570 --> 00:05:34.370 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:05:34.370 --> 00:05:36.240 align:middle line:84%
I mean, was that something
that you have to go through,

00:05:36.240 --> 00:05:39.480 align:middle line:84%
sort of feeling like a victim
or some kind of process

00:05:39.480 --> 00:05:41.550 align:middle line:84%
had been inflicted
on you in some way?

00:05:41.550 --> 00:05:43.510 align:middle line:84%
Well, I think when you're
diagnosed with cancer,

00:05:43.510 --> 00:05:45.450 align:middle line:84%
you just think, well,
why do I have this?

00:05:45.450 --> 00:05:48.187 align:middle line:84%
I mean, and obviously a lot's
to do with the environment,

00:05:48.187 --> 00:05:50.120 align:middle line:84%
and what we've done to the
environment, and the conditions

00:05:50.120 --> 00:05:51.770 align:middle line:90%
of poisoning that we've done.

00:05:51.770 --> 00:05:54.160 align:middle line:84%
But I think there's
also so many factors.

00:05:54.160 --> 00:05:55.960 align:middle line:90%
Was it Tab that I drank?

00:05:55.960 --> 00:05:58.600 align:middle line:90%
Was it cigarettes?

00:05:58.600 --> 00:06:01.020 align:middle line:90%
Was it having a violent father?

00:06:01.020 --> 00:06:04.320 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I think you just try
to process every possibility.

00:06:04.320 --> 00:06:06.610 align:middle line:84%
But I think what
I came to is it's

00:06:06.610 --> 00:06:09.990 align:middle line:84%
probably all those things and
none of those things, you know?

00:06:09.990 --> 00:06:11.840 align:middle line:84%
But one of the things
that happened in chemo

00:06:11.840 --> 00:06:14.820 align:middle line:84%
was that this therapist came,
and she basically gave me

00:06:14.820 --> 00:06:17.640 align:middle line:84%
a frame for the whole
experience, which was she said

00:06:17.640 --> 00:06:19.920 align:middle line:84%
to me, I want you to imagine
that when the poison's entering

00:06:19.920 --> 00:06:22.500 align:middle line:84%
your body that it's
gonna burn away

00:06:22.500 --> 00:06:23.960 align:middle line:90%
everything that needs to go.

00:06:23.960 --> 00:06:25.520 align:middle line:84%
And you're just gonna
burn away your past,

00:06:25.520 --> 00:06:26.860 align:middle line:84%
and you're gonna
burn away any sense

00:06:26.860 --> 00:06:28.100 align:middle line:90%
of victimhood you've ever had.

00:06:28.100 --> 00:06:29.740 align:middle line:84%
And you're gonna
burn away the rapist.

00:06:29.740 --> 00:06:31.370 align:middle line:84%
Because for many,
many years of my life,

00:06:31.370 --> 00:06:33.190 align:middle line:84%
I've been listening to
the stories of women

00:06:33.190 --> 00:06:36.230 align:middle line:84%
around the planet through V-Day,
the global movement, who've

00:06:36.230 --> 00:06:37.670 align:middle line:84%
been raped, and
who've been abused.

00:06:37.670 --> 00:06:39.440 align:middle line:84%
And I think I was
holding a lot of stories

00:06:39.440 --> 00:06:43.120 align:middle line:84%
in my body, which kind of
made a tumor eventually.

00:06:43.120 --> 00:06:45.847 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking about there's
this guy called Gabor Mate.

00:06:45.847 --> 00:06:47.379 align:middle line:84%
Have you heard about him?
-No.

00:06:47.379 --> 00:06:50.950 align:middle line:84%
He's a psychiatrist
in Vancouver.

00:06:50.950 --> 00:06:53.610 align:middle line:84%
He spoke at this conference
I was at about healing.

00:06:53.610 --> 00:06:55.810 align:middle line:84%
And he basically, he's done
a lot of work with Ayahuasca

00:06:55.810 --> 00:06:59.180 align:middle line:84%
also, and ends up with the
theory that a lot of what

00:06:59.180 --> 00:07:02.080 align:middle line:84%
happens to us
physically is based

00:07:02.080 --> 00:07:04.430 align:middle line:84%
on things like
story, and narrative,

00:07:04.430 --> 00:07:06.831 align:middle line:84%
or emotions that get
stored in the body.

00:07:06.831 --> 00:07:08.375 align:middle line:84%
So he talking--
-Oh, he has a book on trauma.

00:07:08.375 --> 00:07:09.074 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, exactly.

00:07:09.074 --> 00:07:11.030 align:middle line:84%
I did meet him at Democracy
Now a few months ago, yes.

00:07:11.030 --> 00:07:11.730 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:07:11.730 --> 00:07:13.090 align:middle line:84%
So he talked about,
for instance,

00:07:13.090 --> 00:07:14.860 align:middle line:84%
how he thinks that
breast cancer is

00:07:14.860 --> 00:07:19.100 align:middle line:84%
often caused from repressed
anger that women feel.

00:07:19.100 --> 00:07:20.960 align:middle line:84%
I think there is
no doubt about it,

00:07:20.960 --> 00:07:23.480 align:middle line:84%
a direct connection
between trauma and disease,

00:07:23.480 --> 00:07:25.880 align:middle line:84%
and particularly reproductive
cancers and sexual abuse.

00:07:25.880 --> 00:07:29.170 align:middle line:84%
And I think years from now,
we'll call cancer trauma.

00:07:29.170 --> 00:07:31.400 align:middle line:84%
We'll be treating it in
very, very similar ways.

00:07:31.400 --> 00:07:34.340 align:middle line:84%
Because my whole experience
was the more I dealt

00:07:34.340 --> 00:07:37.060 align:middle line:84%
with my trauma, and the
more I processed it,

00:07:37.060 --> 00:07:38.640 align:middle line:84%
and the more I released
it, the better I got.

00:07:38.640 --> 00:07:41.600 align:middle line:84%
Now, that's not to say
it's the cure for cancer,

00:07:41.600 --> 00:07:44.160 align:middle line:84%
but I know that there
is a direct correlation

00:07:44.160 --> 00:07:48.340 align:middle line:84%
between me getting sick and
me having unprocessed trauma.

00:07:48.340 --> 00:07:51.080 align:middle line:84%
I've spent my life now
traveling and spending

00:07:51.080 --> 00:07:52.830 align:middle line:84%
years with women
who've been abused,

00:07:52.830 --> 00:07:54.810 align:middle line:84%
and women particularly
on the front lines,

00:07:54.810 --> 00:07:58.100 align:middle line:84%
for example, who hear
stories about rape.

00:07:58.100 --> 00:08:00.570 align:middle line:84%
Last year, I know four
women who got cancer, who

00:08:00.570 --> 00:08:02.600 align:middle line:90%
are doing that kind of work.

00:08:02.600 --> 00:08:04.870 align:middle line:84%
And I think where does
all that go in our bodies?

00:08:04.870 --> 00:08:05.600 align:middle line:90%
Where does it go?

00:08:05.600 --> 00:08:06.730 align:middle line:90%
It goes into our cells.

00:08:06.730 --> 00:08:08.050 align:middle line:90%
It becomes something else.

00:08:08.050 --> 00:08:10.190 align:middle line:84%
And without a way
of talking about it,

00:08:10.190 --> 00:08:12.980 align:middle line:84%
and processing it, and releasing
it, it becomes a disease.

00:08:12.980 --> 00:08:15.170 align:middle line:84%
And particularly in the book,
you talked about the experience

00:08:15.170 --> 00:08:16.570 align:middle line:90%
in the Congo.

00:08:16.570 --> 00:08:17.470 align:middle line:90%
Can you share a little bit?

00:08:17.470 --> 00:08:19.290 align:middle line:84%
I'm not sure everybody's
aware of what's happened

00:08:19.290 --> 00:08:20.770 align:middle line:84%
in the Congo, and
also how it relates

00:08:20.770 --> 00:08:25.210 align:middle line:84%
to the West's infatuation with
technology and so on, also.

00:08:25.210 --> 00:08:28.170 align:middle line:84%
Well, seven years
ago, I was invited

00:08:28.170 --> 00:08:30.170 align:middle line:84%
to the Democratic
Republic of Congo

00:08:30.170 --> 00:08:33.460 align:middle line:84%
by an extraordinary man
named Dr. Denis Mukwege, who

00:08:33.460 --> 00:08:36.179 align:middle line:84%
is one of the noblest,
grandest people on the planet,

00:08:36.179 --> 00:08:39.270 align:middle line:84%
and he's a surgeon and
a doctor at the Panzi

00:08:39.270 --> 00:08:42.090 align:middle line:90%
Hospital in Bukavu, DRC.

00:08:42.090 --> 00:08:47.080 align:middle line:84%
And he's been doing some amazing
work, very, very painful work

00:08:47.080 --> 00:08:50.870 align:middle line:84%
on sewing up women in their
vaginas and their parts

00:08:50.870 --> 00:08:54.530 align:middle line:84%
in the DRC, who are
being massively raped

00:08:54.530 --> 00:08:56.160 align:middle line:84%
in a conflict that
has been raging

00:08:56.160 --> 00:09:00.190 align:middle line:84%
for the last eight years--
I'm sorry, the last 13 years.

00:09:00.190 --> 00:09:03.230 align:middle line:84%
I think we're talking about 8
million people who have died.

00:09:03.230 --> 00:09:05.450 align:middle line:84%
It's estimated that hundreds
and thousands of women

00:09:05.450 --> 00:09:08.150 align:middle line:84%
have been raped, but I think
in the end it will be millions.

00:09:08.150 --> 00:09:11.060 align:middle line:84%
And when I went there, I
had been traveling the world

00:09:11.060 --> 00:09:14.020 align:middle line:84%
for many years supporting
women who are survivors,

00:09:14.020 --> 00:09:17.160 align:middle line:84%
but I'd never seen anything
like what was going on there.

00:09:17.160 --> 00:09:23.160 align:middle line:84%
And the war in Congo is
propelled by natural resources,

00:09:23.160 --> 00:09:25.060 align:middle line:84%
coltan, which goes
into our cellphones

00:09:25.060 --> 00:09:28.810 align:middle line:90%
and PlayStations, copper, tin.

