00:10:28.570 --> 00:10:31.270 align:middle line:84%
But my story became
very interwoven

00:10:31.270 --> 00:10:33.430 align:middle line:84%
with the women of Congo,
because when I went there,

00:10:33.430 --> 00:10:37.030 align:middle line:84%
I made a commitment that V-Day,
movement, would be with them

00:10:37.030 --> 00:10:38.470 align:middle line:90%
until the violence stops.

00:10:38.470 --> 00:10:40.840 align:middle line:84%
And we were in the process
of building this place called

00:10:40.840 --> 00:10:43.700 align:middle line:84%
the City of Joy, which I'm very
happy to say is running now

00:10:43.700 --> 00:10:44.550 align:middle line:90%
and open.

00:10:44.550 --> 00:10:47.420 align:middle line:84%
But it was a place
for women survivors.

00:10:47.420 --> 00:10:49.150 align:middle line:90%
It's a revolutionary center.

00:10:49.150 --> 00:10:50.610 align:middle line:90%
It's a laboratory of love.

00:10:50.610 --> 00:10:55.390 align:middle line:84%
It's really a completely new
concept, where 90 women come

00:10:55.390 --> 00:10:58.000 align:middle line:84%
for six months,
and they are healed

00:10:58.000 --> 00:11:00.630 align:middle line:84%
through therapeutic love,
through dance, through theater,

00:11:00.630 --> 00:11:03.740 align:middle line:84%
through all kinds of
healing, through massage,

00:11:03.740 --> 00:11:06.260 align:middle line:90%
through talk, through touch.

00:11:06.260 --> 00:11:09.870 align:middle line:84%
And then they are trained,
and built, and educated

00:11:09.870 --> 00:11:12.900 align:middle line:84%
to become leaders, who then
return to their communities

00:11:12.900 --> 00:11:15.480 align:middle line:84%
and pass on and lift
up their communities.

00:11:15.480 --> 00:11:17.350 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that sounds so
incredibly important,

00:11:17.350 --> 00:11:20.930 align:middle line:84%
but then I wonder also if more
like the social and structural

00:11:20.930 --> 00:11:24.370 align:middle line:84%
aspects of the situation
aren't changed,

00:11:24.370 --> 00:11:27.300 align:middle line:84%
how will that violence not
keep being perpetuated?

00:11:27.300 --> 00:11:28.730 align:middle line:84%
Well, the answer
to that question is,

00:11:28.730 --> 00:11:31.930 align:middle line:84%
until the structural
changes happen, it won't.

00:11:31.930 --> 00:11:34.980 align:middle line:84%
But how are we gonna
change the structure?

00:11:34.980 --> 00:11:37.930 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we waited for years for
the international community,

00:11:37.930 --> 00:11:39.780 align:middle line:84%
and the governments, and
the leaders of the world

00:11:39.780 --> 00:11:42.840 align:middle line:84%
to stop supporting, for
example, this country, US,

00:11:42.840 --> 00:11:44.710 align:middle line:84%
to stop supporting
Rwanda, which is

00:11:44.710 --> 00:11:47.921 align:middle line:84%
very much responsible for a lot
of the M23s and the militias

00:11:47.921 --> 00:11:48.620 align:middle line:90%
there.

00:11:48.620 --> 00:11:51.140 align:middle line:84%
It's not happening because
the interests are too great.

00:11:51.140 --> 00:11:54.290 align:middle line:10%
I, myself, believe in building
grassroots revolutions,

00:11:54.290 --> 00:11:56.900 align:middle line:10%
and grassroots
forces and energies

00:11:56.900 --> 00:11:58.740 align:middle line:10%
that can begin to
build, and amass

00:11:58.740 --> 00:12:00.410 align:middle line:10%
power, and take things over.

00:12:00.410 --> 00:12:02.210 align:middle line:84%
And I think if we keep
going, in five years,

00:12:02.210 --> 00:12:05.940 align:middle line:84%
we'll have 1,000 women who
are trained and revolutionary,

00:12:05.940 --> 00:12:09.170 align:middle line:84%
who will begin to have impact
on that country and the world.

00:12:09.170 --> 00:12:10.390 align:middle line:90%
I've tried every tactic.

00:12:10.390 --> 00:12:11.704 align:middle line:84%
Do you know, I've
been at the UN.

00:12:11.704 --> 00:12:12.670 align:middle line:90%
I've been at the governments.

00:12:12.670 --> 00:12:13.644 align:middle line:90%
I've been at Downing Street.

00:12:13.644 --> 00:12:14.610 align:middle line:90%
I've been at the White House.

00:12:14.610 --> 00:12:18.720 align:middle line:84%
But where there feels like
there's a yes energetically

00:12:18.720 --> 00:12:24.440 align:middle line:84%
is supporting women who can
drive the future of the Congo.

00:12:24.440 --> 00:12:27.260 align:middle line:84%
And we're seeing
incredible results now

00:12:27.260 --> 00:12:29.040 align:middle line:84%
in women who are
graduating and going back

00:12:29.040 --> 00:12:34.720 align:middle line:84%
to their communities, and really
overhauling the whole culture,

00:12:34.720 --> 00:12:39.030 align:middle line:84%
questioning values, questioning
tradition, demanding rights,

00:12:39.030 --> 00:12:41.480 align:middle line:84%
standing up, and
started cooperatives,

00:12:41.480 --> 00:12:42.830 align:middle line:84%
where they're
feeding their sisters

00:12:42.830 --> 00:12:44.160 align:middle line:90%
and building communities.

00:12:44.160 --> 00:12:47.050 align:middle line:84%
And I have a lot
of faith in women.

00:12:47.050 --> 00:12:48.140 align:middle line:90%
I have a lot of faith in women.

00:12:48.140 --> 00:12:51.030 align:middle line:84%
You basically just began as an
artist, a performance artist,

00:12:51.030 --> 00:12:52.610 align:middle line:90%
and so on, a playwright.

00:12:52.610 --> 00:12:55.840 align:middle line:84%
Did you anticipate moving
into social movement

00:12:55.840 --> 00:12:58.985 align:middle line:84%
organizing or social
movement building in a way?

00:12:58.985 --> 00:13:02.010 align:middle line:84%
You know, I think I've always
been a political activist,

00:13:02.010 --> 00:13:02.830 align:middle line:90%
and an artist.

00:13:02.830 --> 00:13:06.440 align:middle line:84%
And it was always a
hard life to live weave

00:13:06.440 --> 00:13:07.840 align:middle line:90%
together when I was younger.

00:13:07.840 --> 00:13:12.060 align:middle line:84%
Because I think, as a writer,
you don't wanna be didactic,

00:13:12.060 --> 00:13:13.530 align:middle line:84%
and you wanna allow
your characters

00:13:13.530 --> 00:13:14.870 align:middle line:84%
to speak, and have
a point of view

00:13:14.870 --> 00:13:17.250 align:middle line:90%
that's not yours, but theirs.

00:13:17.250 --> 00:13:18.940 align:middle line:84%
I think with "The
Vagina Monologues"

00:13:18.940 --> 00:13:21.290 align:middle line:84%
it was the first
time where I realized

00:13:21.290 --> 00:13:23.450 align:middle line:90%
the worlds could come together.

00:13:23.450 --> 00:13:25.830 align:middle line:84%
I could write a play that
was funny, and disturbing,

00:13:25.830 --> 00:13:29.030 align:middle line:84%
and outrageous,
and what happened

00:13:29.030 --> 00:13:31.620 align:middle line:84%
was, after I started
performing it,

00:13:31.620 --> 00:13:34.790 align:middle line:84%
women would line up after
the show every night.

00:13:34.790 --> 00:13:35.600 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, great.

00:13:35.600 --> 00:13:37.000 align:middle line:84%
They're gonna tell me
about their orgasms,

00:13:37.000 --> 00:13:38.660 align:middle line:84%
and what wonderful
sex lives they have,

00:13:38.660 --> 00:13:40.250 align:middle line:90%
and this is gonna be amazing.

00:13:40.250 --> 00:13:42.620 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, women
lined up to tell me

00:13:42.620 --> 00:13:45.250 align:middle line:84%
how they'd been beaten,
and raped, and gang-raped,

00:13:45.250 --> 00:13:46.980 align:middle line:90%
and abused, and incested.

00:13:46.980 --> 00:13:50.390 align:middle line:84%
And I almost had a break down,
because I felt like I was being

00:13:50.390 --> 00:13:53.810 align:middle line:84%
privy to secrets that they
had never told anyone,

00:13:53.810 --> 00:13:55.460 align:middle line:84%
and they didn't know
what to do with them.

00:13:55.460 --> 00:13:58.350 align:middle line:84%
And I think it was shortly after
that I called a group of women

00:13:58.350 --> 00:14:00.140 align:middle line:84%
together in my living
room, because I think

00:14:00.140 --> 00:14:02.060 align:middle line:84%
all things begin in
small rooms like this,

00:14:02.060 --> 00:14:05.060 align:middle line:84%
where you start the
vision of a new world.

00:14:05.060 --> 00:14:06.780 align:middle line:90%
And I said, I have this play.

00:14:06.780 --> 00:14:10.170 align:middle line:84%
How could we use it
to stop violence?

00:14:10.170 --> 00:14:11.870 align:middle line:84%
And we came up with
V-Day, which was

00:14:11.870 --> 00:14:14.490 align:middle line:90%
Vagina Day, Valentine's Day.

00:14:14.490 --> 00:14:17.150 align:middle line:84%
And we did one performance
of "The Vagina Monologues"

00:14:17.150 --> 00:14:19.320 align:middle line:84%
in New York with all
these amazing performers,

00:14:19.320 --> 00:14:21.540 align:middle line:84%
from Whoopie Goldberg
to Lily Tomlin

00:14:21.540 --> 00:14:22.980 align:middle line:84%
to Susan Sarandon
and Glenn Close.

00:14:22.980 --> 00:14:24.850 align:middle line:84%
And it was like the
theater blew off.

00:14:24.850 --> 00:14:26.690 align:middle line:84%
The roof of the
theater blew off.

00:14:26.690 --> 00:14:28.760 align:middle line:90%
And that was 16 years ago.

00:14:28.760 --> 00:14:32.080 align:middle line:84%
And that has just
spread like wildfire.

00:14:32.080 --> 00:14:35.370 align:middle line:84%
And now V-Day, it's
16 years later.

00:14:35.370 --> 00:14:36.710 align:middle line:90%
We've raised $100 million.

00:14:36.710 --> 00:14:40.510 align:middle line:84%
That has all gone to local
grassroots groups that work

00:14:40.510 --> 00:14:42.590 align:middle line:90%
to stop violence against women.

00:14:42.590 --> 00:14:46.910 align:middle line:84%
And last year, we were able to
birth One Billion Rising, which

00:14:46.910 --> 00:14:49.490 align:middle line:84%
was the biggest-- I
think, it probably

00:14:49.490 --> 00:14:51.240 align:middle line:84%
is the biggest
mass global action

00:14:51.240 --> 00:14:53.810 align:middle line:84%
that's ever happened on
the planet, where a billion

00:14:53.810 --> 00:14:57.770 align:middle line:84%
people rose, and danced, and
did outrageous creative acts

00:14:57.770 --> 00:15:01.890 align:middle line:90%
on February 14th last year.

00:15:01.890 --> 00:15:04.050 align:middle line:84%
And One Billion
Rising was particularly

00:15:04.050 --> 00:15:08.580 align:middle line:84%
an uprising or public outcry
against sexual violence.

00:15:08.580 --> 00:15:10.580 align:middle line:84%
And I think what was really
thrilling about it, because it

00:15:10.580 --> 00:15:13.370 align:middle line:84%
happened in 207
countries, is there

00:15:13.370 --> 00:15:15.460 align:middle line:90%
was enormous intersectionality.

00:15:15.460 --> 00:15:18.330 align:middle line:84%
We saw in the Philippines,
for example, the people who

00:15:18.330 --> 00:15:21.170 align:middle line:84%
were protesting, who
were anti-imperialist

00:15:21.170 --> 00:15:23.230 align:middle line:84%
and against militarization
of bases, which

00:15:23.230 --> 00:15:25.600 align:middle line:84%
is causing sexual
violence, join forces

00:15:25.600 --> 00:15:27.120 align:middle line:90%
with the anti-violence people.

00:15:27.120 --> 00:15:31.240 align:middle line:84%
We saw all over the
world, economic inequality

00:15:31.240 --> 00:15:34.700 align:middle line:84%
and injustice being joined with
anti-violence against women.

00:15:34.700 --> 00:15:38.950 align:middle line:84%
And I think, same with
anti-environmental actions,

00:15:38.950 --> 00:15:42.090 align:middle line:84%
groups that are working to stop
environmental injustice are

00:15:42.090 --> 00:15:45.470 align:middle line:84%
now joining forces with violence
against women activists.

00:15:45.470 --> 00:15:47.470 align:middle line:84%
And I think, to me, that's
the most exciting thing,

00:15:47.470 --> 00:15:51.120 align:middle line:84%
because we're actually building
a much broader-based movement,

00:15:51.120 --> 00:15:53.810 align:middle line:84%
understanding that all these
things are interconnected.

00:15:53.810 --> 00:15:55.550 align:middle line:84%
Like, you can't stop
violence against women

00:15:55.550 --> 00:15:57.550 align:middle line:84%
without looking at
poverty, or racism,

00:15:57.550 --> 00:15:59.750 align:middle line:84%
or environmental injustice,
or economic injustice.

00:15:59.750 --> 00:16:01.040 align:middle line:90%
They're all connected.

00:16:01.040 --> 00:16:03.480 align:middle line:84%
I know you have another event
