00:16:52.920 --> 00:16:54.540 align:middle line:84%
and we're going to
make reparations.

00:16:54.540 --> 00:16:56.140 align:middle line:90%
You know, I've been in Bosnia.

00:16:56.140 --> 00:16:57.830 align:middle line:90%
I have been in Kosovo.

00:16:57.830 --> 00:17:00.110 align:middle line:84%
I have been in every
country in the world,

00:17:00.110 --> 00:17:01.880 align:middle line:84%
where people are
waiting for justice,

00:17:01.880 --> 00:17:03.200 align:middle line:90%
women are waiting for justice.

00:17:03.200 --> 00:17:08.140 align:middle line:84%
And I think until we begin
to look at a justice that

00:17:08.140 --> 00:17:12.150 align:middle line:84%
is a transformative justice, a
justice that doesn't just build

00:17:12.150 --> 00:17:14.240 align:middle line:84%
