00:18:31.290 --> 00:18:32.050 align:middle line:90%
they don't have.

00:18:32.050 --> 00:18:34.940 align:middle line:84%
And so I think a big
part of the movement

00:18:34.940 --> 00:18:36.610 align:middle line:84%
now it is the
engagement of men, and

00:18:36.610 --> 00:18:38.077 align:middle line:90%
working with men as our allies.

00:18:38.077 --> 00:18:39.910 align:middle line:84%
We were talking before,
before we began the interview,

00:18:39.910 --> 00:18:41.914 align:middle line:84%
around the work of
Terrence McKenna,

00:18:41.914 --> 00:18:43.880 align:middle line:84%
and I was kind of surprised,
because it seemed so different

00:18:43.880 --> 00:18:45.200 align:middle line:84%
than your normal
concerns, but you

00:18:45.200 --> 00:18:46.599 align:middle line:84%
were saying that you've
been finding a lot

00:18:46.599 --> 00:18:47.960 align:middle line:90%
of inspiration in his ideas.

00:18:47.960 --> 00:18:49.640 align:middle line:84%
Terrence was a
psychedelic philosopher

00:18:49.640 --> 00:18:53.070 align:middle line:84%
who talked about mushrooms, the
origin of human consciousness,

00:18:53.070 --> 00:18:55.960 align:middle line:84%
and the idea of a
kind of eschaton

00:18:55.960 --> 00:18:58.970 align:middle line:84%
or a kind of redemptive
transformation

00:18:58.970 --> 00:19:00.120 align:middle line:90%
of human society.

00:19:00.120 --> 00:19:02.580 align:middle line:84%
I'm just curious how
that interests you,

00:19:02.580 --> 00:19:06.690 align:middle line:84%
and maybe how that becomes
part of this new paradigm

00:19:06.690 --> 00:19:08.960 align:middle line:84%
or new masculine
construct in a way.

00:19:08.960 --> 00:19:10.920 align:middle line:84%
Well, I think- I'm
actually obsessed right

00:19:10.920 --> 00:19:13.511 align:middle line:84%
now with Terrence McKenna.
-It's his voice.

00:19:13.511 --> 00:19:14.210 align:middle line:90%
His voice is just--

00:19:14.210 --> 00:19:16.970 align:middle line:84%
He's just incredible,
and I think there's so

00:19:16.970 --> 00:19:18.940 align:middle line:84%
many pieces to what
he's talking about,

00:19:18.940 --> 00:19:23.000 align:middle line:84%
but one thing is this whole
idea of cultural engineers.

00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:26.590 align:middle line:84%
I've always been highly suspect
of the culture, the celebrity

00:19:26.590 --> 00:19:29.250 align:middle line:84%
culture and a culture
which has hierarchy,

00:19:29.250 --> 00:19:31.590 align:middle line:84%
and where 1% of
the people matter,

00:19:31.590 --> 00:19:33.240 align:middle line:84%
and the rest of the
people don't matter,

00:19:33.240 --> 00:19:35.250 align:middle line:84%
and they just watch the lives
of celebrities and drool,

00:19:35.250 --> 00:19:36.670 align:middle line:84%
and feel bad, and
hate them, and wanna

00:19:36.670 --> 00:19:38.910 align:middle line:84%
destroy them, because they
don't have what they have.

00:19:38.910 --> 00:19:39.974 align:middle line:90%
And I came back--

00:19:39.974 --> 00:19:41.040 align:middle line:90%
You don't think that's healthy?

00:19:41.040 --> 00:19:43.400 align:middle line:90%
No, somehow, I don't.

00:19:43.400 --> 00:19:45.890 align:middle line:84%
And I came back from Congo,
and I'd been there a month,

00:19:45.890 --> 00:19:53.240 align:middle line:84%
and Congo's just such a--
it's a mind explosion on so

00:19:53.240 --> 00:19:54.790 align:middle line:84%
many levels, because
it's desperately

00:19:54.790 --> 00:19:59.420 align:middle line:84%
poor, and desperately
chaotic, and anarchic,

00:19:59.420 --> 00:20:02.160 align:middle line:84%
but it's also the most beautiful
and most loving people.

00:20:02.160 --> 00:20:05.230 align:middle line:84%
And so whenever I come back,
I'm just flooded for days.

00:20:05.230 --> 00:20:07.390 align:middle line:84%
I don't how to
really adjust to come

00:20:07.390 --> 00:20:09.180 align:middle line:90%
back to New York, particularly.

00:20:09.180 --> 00:20:12.540 align:middle line:84%
And I was thinking--
I don't know.

00:20:12.540 --> 00:20:15.120 align:middle line:84%
I think the reason Terrence is
really speaking to me lately

00:20:15.120 --> 00:20:18.590 align:middle line:84%
is I started to watch some TV
shows that were happening here,

00:20:18.590 --> 00:20:21.090 align:middle line:90%
and I just got so freaked out.

00:20:21.090 --> 00:20:22.880 align:middle line:84%
Every show just
seemed so cynical,

00:20:22.880 --> 00:20:26.320 align:middle line:84%
and the worse of
people, and celebrating

00:20:26.320 --> 00:20:30.960 align:middle line:84%
the worst of people, and
this ongoing cynicism.

00:20:30.960 --> 00:20:32.970 align:middle line:84%
And I think what
Terrence-- I just

00:20:32.970 --> 00:20:34.610 align:middle line:90%
love what he says, just unplug.

00:20:34.610 --> 00:20:35.560 align:middle line:90%
Like, refuse it.

00:20:35.560 --> 00:20:36.420 align:middle line:90%
Don't watch it.

00:20:36.420 --> 00:20:38.186 align:middle line:84%
Well, he also says culture
is your operating system.

00:20:38.186 --> 00:20:40.650 align:middle line:84%
Absolutely, but he also
says, it's not your friend.

00:20:40.650 --> 00:20:44.040 align:middle line:84%
It's your enemy, and
create your own culture.

00:20:44.040 --> 00:20:44.750 align:middle line:90%
Go out.

00:20:44.750 --> 00:20:45.950 align:middle line:84%
Like, that's why
I love this show.

00:20:45.950 --> 00:20:47.650 align:middle line:84%
Go out, and make
something that's

00:20:47.650 --> 00:20:49.940 align:middle line:84%
coming from your own heart,
and your own artistry,

00:20:49.940 --> 00:20:52.910 align:middle line:84%
and your own self, and
trust your small community.

00:20:52.910 --> 00:20:54.720 align:middle line:84%
Trust the smallness
of the community,

00:20:54.720 --> 00:20:56.430 align:middle line:84%
that there'll be many other
small communities that

00:20:56.430 --> 00:20:57.800 align:middle line:90%
will begin to create something.

00:20:57.800 --> 00:21:00.640 align:middle line:84%
And I think One Billion
Rising has really taught

00:21:00.640 --> 00:21:02.937 align:middle line:90%
me that if you give people--

00:21:02.937 --> 00:21:04.770 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you don't think
we're gonna give Johnny Carson

00:21:04.770 --> 00:21:06.450 align:middle line:84%
a run for his money here?
-You know what?

00:21:06.450 --> 00:21:08.940 align:middle line:84%
I actually do, but I think it
will come in a different kind

00:21:08.940 --> 00:21:12.400 align:middle line:84%
of way, hopefully, that it
won't be based on people selling

00:21:12.400 --> 00:21:15.240 align:middle line:84%
while you're talking, and it
won't be based on transactions,

00:21:15.240 --> 00:21:17.027 align:middle line:84%
but it will be based
on transformation.

00:21:17.027 --> 00:21:19.160 align:middle line:84%
Let's just talk about this idea
of cultural engineering for one

00:21:19.160 --> 00:21:20.890 align:middle line:84%
second, and then we're
gonna take a little break

00:21:20.890 --> 00:21:23.980 align:middle line:84%
and come back with
you and another guest.

00:21:23.980 --> 00:21:28.650 align:middle line:84%
Well, you know, everything
I've ever done in my life

00:21:28.650 --> 00:21:32.140 align:middle line:84%
that I've been happy
about has been accidental.

00:21:32.140 --> 00:21:36.400 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's come
from curiosity.

00:21:36.400 --> 00:21:38.460 align:middle line:84%
It's come from-- like, I was
really interested in vaginas,

00:21:38.460 --> 00:21:40.020 align:middle line:84%
so I started to
write about vaginas.

00:21:40.020 --> 00:21:42.000 align:middle line:84%
I had no desire to do
a play about vaginas.

00:21:42.000 --> 00:21:43.540 align:middle line:90%
It was just, like, wow.

00:21:43.540 --> 00:21:45.920 align:middle line:84%
Women were telling incredible
stories about their vaginas,

00:21:45.920 --> 00:21:47.350 align:middle line:84%
and I was just
writing them down.

00:21:47.350 --> 00:21:49.610 align:middle line:84%
And then it started to
grow into something.

00:21:49.610 --> 00:21:51.240 align:middle line:84%
Now, people told
me when I began,

00:21:51.240 --> 00:21:52.680 align:middle line:84%
no one will ever
come to this play.

00:21:52.680 --> 00:21:53.860 align:middle line:90%
Change the title.

00:21:53.860 --> 00:21:55.430 align:middle line:84%
I kept saying, what
am I gonna call it?

00:21:55.430 --> 00:21:56.620 align:middle line:90%
The Pocketbook Monologues?

00:21:56.620 --> 00:21:58.526 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it's about vaginas.

00:21:58.526 --> 00:22:01.030 align:middle line:84%
It's not gonna be like one
of those gotcha things.

00:22:01.030 --> 00:22:02.580 align:middle line:84%
You get in the theater,
and it's like gotcha!

00:22:02.580 --> 00:22:04.300 align:middle line:90%
It's vaginas!

00:22:04.300 --> 00:22:08.180 align:middle line:84%
But one of the things I
discovered along the way

00:22:08.180 --> 00:22:11.890 align:middle line:84%
is that when you do that thing
that you're most interested in,

00:22:11.890 --> 00:22:14.280 align:middle line:84%
and it is really
connected to some part

00:22:14.280 --> 00:22:16.200 align:middle line:84%
of your being and
your soul, it actually

00:22:16.200 --> 00:22:17.830 align:middle line:90%
resonates with other people.

00:22:17.830 --> 00:22:20.240 align:middle line:84%
If you told me when I started
the "The Vagina Monologues"

00:22:20.240 --> 00:22:23.490 align:middle line:84%
20 years ago that it
would be in 50 languages,

00:22:23.490 --> 00:22:26.070 align:middle line:84%
that it would've been
formed in 207 countries,

00:22:26.070 --> 00:22:28.780 align:middle line:84%
tha-- I've seen it
done in Pakistan.

00:22:28.780 --> 00:22:30.650 align:middle line:90%
I've seen it in China.

00:22:30.650 --> 00:22:32.110 align:middle line:90%
It's been done everywhere.

00:22:32.110 --> 00:22:33.510 align:middle line:90%
Why did that happen?

00:22:33.510 --> 00:22:37.330 align:middle line:84%
There's some phenomena aspect
to it that is way beyond me.

00:22:37.330 --> 00:22:41.380 align:middle line:84%
But it has to do with curiosity,
and following a desire

00:22:41.380 --> 00:22:43.160 align:middle line:84%
to know something,
and just going

00:22:43.160 --> 00:22:47.540 align:middle line:84%
with that, as opposed to
editing it, or challenging it.

00:22:47.540 --> 00:22:50.020 align:middle line:84%
And it was the same thing
with One Billion Rising.

00:22:50.020 --> 00:22:53.470 align:middle line:84%
I was like, look, there are one
billion women on the planet,

00:22:53.470 --> 00:22:56.020 align:middle line:84%
one out of three, who
have been raped or beaten,

00:22:56.020 --> 00:22:58.000 align:middle line:90%
one billion women on the planet.

00:22:58.000 --> 00:22:58.860 align:middle line:90%
One billion!

00:22:58.860 --> 00:22:59.910 align:middle line:90%
What is a billion?

00:22:59.910 --> 00:23:01.440 align:middle line:84%
I kept thinking, like,
what is a billion?

00:23:01.440 --> 00:23:02.620 align:middle line:90%
I would lie in bed at night.

00:23:02.620 --> 00:23:04.440 align:middle line:84%
And then one day I said,
well, what if we just invited

00:23:04.440 --> 00:23:06.030 align:middle line:90%
a billion people to dance?

00:23:06.030 --> 00:23:08.540 align:middle line:84%
Just to dance, and to say,
I'm releasing the shackles.

00:23:08.540 --> 00:23:09.640 align:middle line:90%
I'm gonna go on the streets.

00:23:09.640 --> 00:23:10.650 align:middle line:90%
I'm gonna go in my church.

00:23:10.650 --> 00:23:11.527 align:middle line:90%
I'm gonna go in my mosque.

00:23:11.527 --> 00:23:12.760 align:middle line:84%
I'm gonna go everywhere
in the world,

00:23:12.760 --> 00:23:18.210 align:middle line:84%
and just release these
shackles of bondage, of rape,

00:23:18.210 --> 00:23:19.140 align:middle line:90%
and torture.

00:23:19.140 --> 00:23:19.955 align:middle line:90%
And you know what?

00:23:19.955 --> 00:23:20.790 align:middle line:90%
It happened.

00:23:20.790 --> 00:23:22.750 align:middle line:84%
Now, I have no idea
how it happened.

00:23:22.750 --> 00:23:24.670 align:middle line:84%
You can say the internet, but
that's not how it happened.

00:23:24.670 --> 00:23:27.031 align:middle line:84%
It happened because I
listened to an instinct,

00:23:27.031 --> 00:23:28.430 align:middle line:84%
then other people
listened to an instinct.

00:23:28.430 --> 00:23:29.720 align:middle line:84%
They took it.
They made it theirs.

00:23:29.720 --> 00:23:32.610 align:middle line:84%
Everybody made it theirs, and
it just flew around the world.

00:23:32.610 --> 00:23:35.210 align:middle line:84%
And I think the
cultural engineers don't

00:23:35.210 --> 00:23:37.160 align:middle line:90%
want that to happen, right?

00:23:37.160 --> 00:23:40.500 align:middle line:84%
They have us hooked into a
system of buy-sell cynicism,

00:23:40.500 --> 00:23:41.850 align:middle line:90%
buy-sell cynicism.

00:23:41.850 --> 00:23:42.720 align:middle line:90%
It's all bad.

00:23:42.720 --> 00:23:44.120 align:middle line:90%
You can't change anything.

00:23:44.120 --> 00:23:45.620 align:middle line:90%
You won't ever change the world.

00:23:45.620 --> 00:23:47.240 align:middle line:84%
If you believe you
can change the world,

00:23:47.240 --> 00:23:50.260 align:middle line:84%
you're somehow treated as
less than, and not cool,

00:23:50.260 --> 00:23:52.270 align:middle line:90%
and outside.

00:23:52.270 --> 00:23:54.320 align:middle line:84%
I can't even tell you how many
snarky things have been said

00:23:54.320 --> 00:23:56.560 align:middle line:84%
about my life, or me,
because I actually believe

00:23:56.560 --> 00:23:57.910 align:middle line:90%
we can make the world better.

00:23:57.910 --> 00:24:01.580 align:middle line:84%
And that's just part of that
same cultural engineering

00:24:01.580 --> 00:24:03.600 align:middle line:90%
that keeps everybody depressed.

00:24:03.600 --> 00:24:05.110 align:middle line:84%
I mean, what did I
read the other day?

00:24:05.110 --> 00:24:08.710 align:middle line:84%
That more people are
depressed in America?

00:24:08.710 --> 00:24:12.970 align:middle line:84%
It will be the second
disability in five years.

00:24:12.970 --> 00:24:14.180 align:middle line:90%
Depression?

00:24:14.180 --> 00:24:15.760 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's how many
people are depressed

00:24:15.760 --> 00:24:18.010 align:middle line:90%
in this country of plenty?

00:24:18.010 --> 00:24:22.470 align:middle line:10%
So I think part of it is,
how do you unplug from that,

00:24:22.470 --> 00:24:25.480 align:middle line:10%
and begin to listen to your own
voice, and your own instincts,

00:24:25.480 --> 00:24:29.050 align:middle line:10%
and your own wisdom, and
start creating based on that

00:24:29.050 --> 00:24:32.640 align:middle line:10%
without approval, and
without seeking approval

00:24:32.640 --> 00:24:36.154 align:middle line:10%
from those cultural engineers?
-Awesome.

00:24:36.154 --> 00:24:37.220 align:middle line:90%
Well, listen, thank you so much.

00:24:37.220 --> 00:24:39.130 align:middle line:84%
We're gonna have you back in a
few minutes with another guest.

00:24:39.130 --> 00:24:40.053 align:middle line:84%
It's so wonderful
to talk to you,

00:24:40.053 --> 00:24:41.219 align:middle line:84%
and it's amazing
work you're doing.

